{"key":"processedPost-10686858","value":{"id":10686858,"first":10685628,"last":10697625,"when":1247753892,"utime":"07/16/09 05:18 PM","cleanedPost":"As long as the drywall isn't from China, or greenboard made for kitchens and bathrooms, it will work fine.&nbsp; There is no reason to get food grade gypsum.&nbsp; We grow mushrooms on horse manure and it sure isn't food grade.<br />You don't lime substrates because their pH is fine as is.&nbsp; Gypsum isn't added to alter the pH.&nbsp; Use lime and gypsum in casing layers if you use one, but use only gypsum in substrates.<br />Why would most vendors stock something that can be found in nearly every nursery for half or less the price?&nbsp; I get 50 pound bags of gypsum for $8 locally, and there's no shipping charge.<br />Clean up this thread, and type correctly.&nbsp; This isn't a chat room.&nbsp; It's a place to share technical information on complex tasks, which doesn't lend itself well to pre-teen ghetto slang.<br />RR"}}